@page "/profile/chiquito"

<h2 class="text-center">Meet Chiquito: Your New Best Friend</h2>

<div class="text-center mt-4">
    <!-- Large Image of the Dog -->
    <img src="https://images.saymedia-content.com/.image/ar_4:3%2Cc_fill%2Ccs_srgb%2Cfl_progressive%2Cq_auto:eco%2Cw_1200/MjA2NjY5MjQ4Mzg1MjYyNzk2/why-would-a-house-trained-dog-start-pooping-in-the-house.jpg"
         alt="Chiquito"
         class="img-fluid"
         style="width: 500px; height: 500px; object-fit: cover;">
</div>

<!-- Long Description Section -->
<div class="container mt-4">
    <p>
        Meet Chiquito, a sweet, resilient, and affectionate terrier mix looking for a loving and stable forever home. With her bright eyes, perky ears,
        and loving personality, Chiquito is the perfect companion for anyone willing to give her the second chance she deserves.
    </p>
    <p>
        Chiquito’s story is unlike any other. She came from Culiacán, Sinaloa where her previous owners were entangled in a dangerous world of cartel business.
        Unfortunately, their lifestyle led them down a treacherous path, and ultimately, Chiquito found herself caught up in their unstable circumstances. Despite this rocky start,
        she has proven to be an incredibly loving, loyal, and trusting dog who sees only the best in her new journey ahead.
    </p>
    <p>
        Terriers are known for their spirited personalities, independence, and intelligence—and Chiquito embodies all of these traits. She’s eager to explore her surroundings,
        loves attention from her humans, and can make the perfect playmate or cuddling partner for anyone who offers her the care and routine she craves.
    </p>
    <p>
        Chiquito would thrive in a calm, loving home that prioritizes stability and attention. While she may have experienced hardship in her past, her heart is open and full of potential.
        She gets along wonderfully with people, other pets, and would fit beautifully into a variety of households willing to provide her with the patience and love she needs to feel safe.
    </p>
    <p>
        If you’ve got space in your heart and home for a brave, loving soul who has weathered storms and come out stronger, Chiquito may just be the best thing to happen to your family.
        With her charming personality, loyal heart, and beautiful spirit, she is ready to leave her past behind and embark on her next adventure with YOU.
    </p>

    <!-- Centered Button Section -->
    <div class="text-center mt-3">
        <form action="/submit" method="POST">
            <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="window.location.href='/application-page'; return false;">Submit Application</button>
        </form>
    </div>
</div>

